# WHAT IT IS
#   Lunite is "a modern hybrid programming language that blends
#   Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) and Procedural-Oriented
#   Programming (POP) paradigms".  Built in Python (the
#   reference interpreter is `lunite.py`), with a custom Lunite
#   Bytecode Virtual Machine (LBVM) for `.lunb` compiled
#   bytecode artifacts.  Lunite source uses the `.luna`
#   extension and supports both the interpreted-execution path
#   (fastest dev loop) and the compile-to-bytecode "binded"
#   workflow (faster start-up, distributable artifact).
#
#   Notable features:
#     • Preprocessor with `#include`-style directives + macros
#     • Hybrid OOP+POP type system
#     • `sandbox` mode that restricts I/O / filesystem / network
#       access for executing untrusted scripts
#     • `debug` mode that prints tokens, AST, environment
#       state, and per-instruction execution trace
#     • `build` interactive wizard that bundles a `.luna`
#       source + dependencies + LBVM runtime into a single
#       distributable artifact
#     • Transpile-to-C++ companion path (separate guide;
#       produces a native interpreter ~2-3x faster than the
#       Python reference)
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from lunite.py `main()`
#                       function; extracted via `gh api repos/
#                       SubhrajitSain/Lunite/contents/
#                       lunite.py`)
#
#   lunite [<SUBCOMMAND> [<FILE.luna>]]
#
#   No arguments:                    Start the interactive REPL
#                                    (`start_repl()`)
#
#   Subcommands:
#     run <FILE.luna>                Execute the source file
#                                    through the standard
#                                    interpreter
#     compile <FILE.luna>            Compile the source file to
#                                    `.lunb` Lunite-bytecode
#                                    (LBVM format)
#     debug <FILE.luna>              Run the source file with
#                                    full debug tracing —
#                                    prints tokens, AST,
#                                    environment, and per-
#                                    instruction execution log
#     sandbox <FILE.luna>            Run the source file in
#                                    sandbox mode with
#                                    restricted I/O / FS /
#                                    network capability
#     build                          Interactive build wizard
#                                    (bundles source +
#                                    dependencies + LBVM
#                                    runtime into a single
#                                    distributable artifact;
#                                    prompts for the source
#                                    file)
#     clean                          Clean build artifacts /
#                                    cached bytecode from the
#                                    current directory
#     version                        Print Lunite version
#                                    information
#
